com.facebook.buck.parser

Class Parser

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.buck.parser.Parser

  • public class Parser
extends Object
    High-level build file parsing machinery. Primarily responsible for producing a ActionGraph based on a set of targets. Also exposes some low-level facilities to parse individual build files. Caches build rules to minimise the number of calls to python and processes filesystem WatchEvents to invalidate the cache as files change. Expected to be used from a single thread, so methods are not synchronized or thread safe.

        Parameters:

      • filterTargetsInProjectFromRoots

        public Iterable<BuildTarget> filterTargetsInProjectFromRoots(Iterable<BuildTarget> roots,
                                                    Iterable<String> defaultIncludes,
                                                    BuckEventBus eventBus,
                                                    RawRulePredicate filter)
                                                      throws BuildFileParseException,
                                                             BuildTargetException,
                                                             IOException,
                                                             InterruptedException
        Takes a sequence of build targets and parses all of the build files that contain them and their transitive deps, producing a collection of "raw rules" that have been produced from the build files. The specified RawRulePredicate is applied to this collection. This method returns the collection of BuildTargets that correspond to the raw rules that were matched by the predicate.

        Because project_config rules are not transitive dependencies of rules such as android_binary, but are defined in the same build files as the transitive dependencies of an android_binary, this method is helpful in finding all of the project_config rules needed to produce an IDE configuration to build said android_binary. See RawRulePredicates.matchBuildRuleType(BuildRuleType) for an example of such a RawRulePredicate.

        Throws:
        BuildFileParseException
        BuildTargetException
        IOException
        InterruptedException
